5. Remediation

To secure the Redis installation, it is recommended to:

    Enable Authentication: Set a strong password in the redis.conf file using the requirepass directive.

    Bind to Localhost: Ensure Redis only listens on 127.0.0.1 unless remote access is strictly necessary.

    Rename Dangerous Commands: Use the rename-command configuration to hide commands like CONFIG, KEYS, and FLUSHALL.</Target_IP></Target_IP>
